    WHY  : Variance is the mathematical building block behind std and many
           statistical/ML formulas (e.g. variance of predictions).
    WHEN : Use when a formula specifically requires variance rather than
           standard deviation (they're closely related but not the same units).
    """
    header("f_var() -> arr.var()")
    arr = np.array([2, 4, 4, 4, 5, 5, 7, 9])
    print("arr:", arr)
